1
00:00:30,463 --> 00:00:31,725
(woman)
Earth-That-Was..

2
00:00:31,798 --> 00:00:34,926
could no longer sustain
our numbers, we were so many.

3
00:00:38,438 --> 00:00:40,633
We found a new solar system:

4
00:00:41,107 --> 00:00:43,905
dozens of planets
and hundreds of moons.

5
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:48,979
Each one terraformed,
a process taking decades...

6
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:52,212
to support human life.
To be new Earths.

7
00:00:52,786 --> 00:00:55,152
The central planets
formed the Alliance.

8
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:57,583
Ruled by an interplanetary
parliament...

9
00:00:57,657 --> 00:01:00,125
the Alliance was
a beacon of civilization.

10
00:01:01,294 --> 00:01:03,922
The savage outer planets
were not so enlightened...

11
00:01:03,997 --> 00:01:06,022
and refused Alliance control.

12
00:01:06,699 --> 00:01:09,065
The war was devastating.

13
00:01:09,869 --> 00:01:12,064
But the Alliance's victory
over the Independents...

14
00:01:12,138 --> 00:01:14,003
ensured a safer universe.

15
00:01:14,207 --> 00:01:16,402
And now, everyone
can enjoy the comfort...

16
00:01:16,476 --> 00:01:18,774
and enlightenment
of true civilization.

17
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:21,880
Why were the lndependents
even fighting us?

18
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:23,916
Why wouldn't they look
to be more civilized?

19
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:26,577
I hear they're cannibals.
That's only Reavers.

20
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:28,780
Reavers aren't real.
Full well they are.

21
00:01:28,855 --> 00:01:30,686
I heard they attack settlers
from space...

22
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,190
and kill them,
and wear their skins...

23
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,419
and rape them
for hours and hours--

24
00:01:34,494 --> 00:01:35,586
[speaking Chinese]

25
00:01:35,728 --> 00:01:36,752
[birds chirping]

26
00:01:36,830 --> 00:01:40,425
It's true
that there are dangers
on the outer planets.

27
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:43,035
So with so many social
and medical advancements...

28
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,196
we can bring
to the lndependents...

29
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:47,102
why would they fight
so hard against us?

30
00:01:47,173 --> 00:01:48,265
We meddle.

31
00:01:48,842 --> 00:01:49,831
River?

32
00:01:50,577 --> 00:01:52,602
People don't like
to be meddled with.

33
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:54,806
We tell them what to do,
what to think.

34
00:01:54,881 --> 00:01:56,473
Don't run, don't walk.

35
00:01:56,983 --> 00:02:00,441
We're in their homes
and in their heads
and we haven't the right.

36
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,885
We're meddlesome.

37
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:06,453
River, we're not telling
people what to think...

38
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,288
we're just trying
to show them how.

39
00:02:09,863 --> 00:02:10,887
[screaming]

40
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,660
(Dr. Mathias)
She's dreaming. Got that?
Off the charts.

41
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,262
Scary monsters.

42
00:02:15,335 --> 00:02:17,360
Let's amp it up.
Delcium, eight drop.

43
00:02:17,437 --> 00:02:18,426
[panting]

44
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:21,866
See, most of our best work
is done when they're asleep.

45
00:02:21,941 --> 00:02:24,501
We can monitor and direct
their subconscious...

46
00:02:24,577 --> 00:02:26,272
implant suggestions.

47
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:30,173
It's a little startling
to see at first,
but results are spectacular.

48
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,717
Especially in this case.
River Tam is our star pupil.

49
00:02:33,786 --> 00:02:35,151
I've heard that.

50
00:02:35,255 --> 00:02:37,120
She'll be ideal
for defense deployment...

51
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:38,987
even with the side effects.

52
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:40,585
Tell me about them.

53
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:43,151
Well, obviously,
she's unstable.

54
00:02:43,263 --> 00:02:46,027
The neural stripping
does tend to fragment...

55
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:47,657
their own reality matrix.

56
00:02:47,734 --> 00:02:49,861
It manifests as borderline--
What use do we have...

57
00:02:49,936 --> 00:02:51,631
for a psychic
if she's insane?

58
00:02:51,704 --> 00:02:53,604
[groaning]
(Dr. Mathias)
She's not just a psychic.

59
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,233
Given the right trigger,
this girl is a living weapon.

60
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:59,904
She has her lucid periods.
We're hoping
to improve upon the....

61
00:03:01,147 --> 00:03:03,581
I'm sorry, sir,
but I have to ask.

62
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:06,141
Is there a reason
for this inspection?

63
00:03:06,419 --> 00:03:08,114
Am I making you nervous?

64
00:03:08,655 --> 00:03:11,647
Key members of Parliament
have personally
observed this subject.

65
00:03:11,724 --> 00:03:13,624
I was told that
the Alliance's support...

66
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:15,160
for the project
was unanimous.

67
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:18,595
The demonstration
of her power--
How is she physically?

68
00:03:18,731 --> 00:03:20,426
Like nothing we've seen.

69
00:03:21,334 --> 00:03:24,895
All our subjects
are conditioned for combat,
but River...

70
00:03:26,005 --> 00:03:28,838
she's a creature
of extraordinary grace.

71
00:03:29,475 --> 00:03:30,874
Yes.

72
00:03:32,011 --> 00:03:34,104
She always
did love to dance.

73
00:03:38,251 --> 00:03:40,344
River, it's Simon.

74
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,709
[moaning]

75
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:44,790
Please, it's Simon.

76
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:47,615
It's your brother.

77
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:56,390
Simon.

78
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:00,497
They know you've come.

79
00:04:01,307 --> 00:04:03,275
[machines beeping]

80
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:08,170
We can't make it
to the surface from inside.

81
00:04:10,783 --> 00:04:12,045
Find out.

82
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:25,653
[grunting]

83
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,662
[wind howling]

84
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:45,879
(man)
A subject is loose,
security breach. Shaft 7.

85
00:05:03,202 --> 00:05:04,191
(The Operative)
Stop.

86
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:07,939
Backtrack. Stop.

87
00:05:20,286 --> 00:05:21,514
Excuse me...

88
00:05:21,587 --> 00:05:23,578
no one is allowed
in the records room...

89
00:05:23,656 --> 00:05:25,419
without my express permission.

90
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:28,722
Forgive me, but I prefer
to see the event alone,
without...

91
00:05:29,896 --> 00:05:30,885
bias.

92
00:05:30,963 --> 00:05:34,262
I need to see your clearance.
And you are right
to insist.

93
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:36,358
[beeping]

94
00:05:36,703 --> 00:05:39,399
(woman)
Parliamentary override.
Full access.

95
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:40,831
Apologies.

96
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:42,169
An operative of
the Parliament...

97
00:05:42,241 --> 00:05:44,607
will, of course,
have full cooperation.

98
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:46,635
I'm not sure what....

99
00:05:47,947 --> 00:05:51,110
I see no listing
of rank or name.
I have neither.

100
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:55,282
Like this facility,
I don't exist.

101
00:05:55,588 --> 00:05:57,351
Let's talk about the Tams.

102
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,654
I assume you've
scanned the status logs--

103
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:02,820
River was your greatest
success. A prodigy.

104
00:06:03,262 --> 00:06:05,093
A phenomenon.

105
00:06:05,298 --> 00:06:08,495
Until her brother
walked in here
and took her from you.

106
00:06:08,735 --> 00:06:11,397
It's not quite so simple.
I'm well aware of that.

107
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,304
There was no way
that I could--
No. No. Of course.

108
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:16,365
The boy spent
his entire fortune
developing...

109
00:06:16,442 --> 00:06:18,137
the contacts
to infiltrate this place.

110
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,736
Gave up a brilliant future
in medicine as well.

111
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:23,077
It's madness.
Madness?

112
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:26,679
Have you looked
at this scan carefully,
Doctor?

113
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:29,079
At his face?

114
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:34,589
It's love, in point of fact.

115
00:06:35,194 --> 00:06:37,389
Something a good deal
more dangerous.

116
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:38,621
Why are you here?

117
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:43,328
Because the situation
is even less simple
than you think.

118
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:47,264
Do you know what your sin is,
Doctor?

119
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,405
I wonder if--
It's pride.

120
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:59,214
Key members of Parliament
have personally
observed this subject.

121
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:02,013
I was told that
the Alliance's support--

122
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:06,585
"Key members of Parliament."

123
00:07:09,729 --> 00:07:10,889
Key.

124
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:14,129
The minds behind
every military...

125
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,760
diplomatic,
and covert operation...

126
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:19,498
in the galaxy,
and you put them...

127
00:07:19,572 --> 00:07:22,006
in a room with a psychic.

128
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:27,374
If there was some
classified information
that she....

129
00:07:27,513 --> 00:07:29,447
She never spoke of it.
I don't know what it is.

130
00:07:29,515 --> 00:07:30,573
Nor do l.

131
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,618
And judging by
her deteriorating
mental state...

132
00:07:32,685 --> 00:07:33,947
I'd say we're both
better off.

133
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,648
Secrets are not my concern.

134
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,823
Keeping them is.

135
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:44,522
Whatever secrets
she might have
accidentally gleaned...

136
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:47,065
it's probable
she doesn't even
know she knows them.

137
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,863
That they're buried
beneath layers of psychosis.

138
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:54,837
You know, in certain
older civilized cultures...

139
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:57,099
when men failed as entirely...

140
00:07:57,176 --> 00:07:59,667
as you have,
they would throw themselves...

141
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:00,971
on their swords.

142
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:03,641
Well, unfortunately,
I forgot to bring a sword.

143
00:08:06,786 --> 00:08:09,584
I would put that down
right now, if I were you.

144
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:12,681
Would you be killed
in your sleep
like an ailing pet?

145
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,483
[grunting]

146
00:08:15,895 --> 00:08:16,884
[yelling]

147
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,324
[screaming]

148
00:08:24,704 --> 00:08:26,103
(The Operative)
Young miss....

149
00:08:29,909 --> 00:08:33,572
Young miss, I'll need
all the logs on behavioral
modification triggers.

150
00:08:33,646 --> 00:08:35,079
We'll have to reach out
to River Tam...

151
00:08:35,147 --> 00:08:36,580
and help her
to come back to us.

152
00:08:36,649 --> 00:08:38,810
No matter how
far out Simon has....

153
00:08:39,151 --> 00:08:40,175
[gasping]

154
00:08:40,253 --> 00:08:41,948
This is a good death.

155
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:43,410
[gasping]

156
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,321
There's no shame in this...

157
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:51,594
in a man's death.
A man who has done fine works.

158
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,863
We're making a better world.

159
00:08:57,403 --> 00:08:58,665
All of them...

160
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:01,963
better worlds.

161
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:10,514
Young miss,
I need you to go to work now.

162
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:14,450
I think I may have
a long way to travel.

163
00:09:23,863 --> 00:09:28,425
Where are you hiding,
little girl?

164
00:10:24,056 --> 00:10:25,114
[explosion]

165
00:10:25,224 --> 00:10:26,213
[alarm buzzing]

166
00:10:26,325 --> 00:10:29,055
What was that?
Did you see that?

167
00:10:32,531 --> 00:10:33,725
Was that the primary
buffer panel?

168
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:36,063
It did seem to resemble--
Did the primary
buffer panel...

169
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:39,104
just fall off my gorramn ship
for no apparent reason?

170
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,064
Looks like.

171
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,699
I thought Kaylee checked
the entry couplings.

172
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:45,767
I've a clear memory of it.
If she doesn't get us...

173
00:10:45,845 --> 00:10:48,405
extra flow
from the engine room
to offset the burn-through...

174
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,108
this landing is gonna
get pretty interesting.

175
00:10:50,182 --> 00:10:53,117
Define "interesting."
"Oh, God,
we're all gonna die?"

176
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,812
This is the captain.
We have a little problem...

177
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:59,983
with our entry sequence,
so we may experience some...

178
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:02,425
slight turbulence
and then explode.

179
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,019
Can you shave the vector?
I'm doing it!

180
00:11:04,096 --> 00:11:06,758
It's not enough.
Just get us on the ground!

181
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:09,232
That part will happen
pretty definitely.

182
00:11:10,102 --> 00:11:12,536
We're gonna explode?
I don't wanna explode.

183
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:14,197
Jayne, how many weapons
you plan on taking?

184
00:11:14,273 --> 00:11:16,173
You only got two arms.
I just get excitable...

185
00:11:16,242 --> 00:11:18,142
as to choice.
Like to have my options open.

186
00:11:18,210 --> 00:11:20,542
I don't plan on any shooting
taking place during this job.

187
00:11:20,613 --> 00:11:24,208
What you plan
and what takes place ain't
ever exactly been similar.

188
00:11:24,283 --> 00:11:26,683
No grenades.

189
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:29,013
We crashing again?
(Mal)
Talk to your husband.

190
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:30,316
Mule prepped?
Good to go, sir.

191
00:11:30,389 --> 00:11:31,378
Just loading her up.

192
00:11:31,457 --> 00:11:32,481
Those grenades?

193
00:11:32,558 --> 00:11:33,957
(Jayne)
Yeah, Captain
doesn't want them.

194
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:36,551
Jayne, we're robbing
the place. We're not
occupying it.

195
00:11:36,762 --> 00:11:38,024
[crashing]

196
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,464
Kaylee!

197
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:48,933
Kaylee, what in the sphincter
of hell are you playing at?

198
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:50,976
We got the primary
buffer panel coming right--

199
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:53,307
Everything's shiny, Captain.
Not to fret.

200
00:11:54,113 --> 00:11:56,843
You told me
those entry couplings
would hold for another week!

201
00:11:56,916 --> 00:12:00,909
That was six months ago,
Captain.
My ship don't crash.

202
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:03,415
If she crashes,
you crashed her.

203
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:07,216
Doctor.

204
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:11,023
Guess who needs
to get innocked
before we hit planet-side.

205
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:13,292
Bit of a rockety ride.

206
00:12:13,365 --> 00:12:15,833
Nothing to be worried about.
I'm not worried.

207
00:12:16,168 --> 00:12:18,159
Fear is nothing to
be ashamed of, Doctor.

208
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:20,831
This isn't fear.
This is anger.

209
00:12:21,874 --> 00:12:26,072
Well, kind of hard to tell
one from the other,
face like yours.

210
00:12:26,612 --> 00:12:29,445
Well, I imagine
if it were fear,
my eyes would be wider.

211
00:12:29,882 --> 00:12:31,281
I'll keep a lookout
for that next time.

212
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:32,647
You're not taking her.

213
00:12:32,718 --> 00:12:35,585
No, no, this is not
a thing I'm interested
in talking over with--

214
00:12:35,654 --> 00:12:37,952
She's not going with you,
and that's final.

215
00:12:38,023 --> 00:12:40,992
I hear the words
"that's final" come
out your mouth ever again...

216
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,527
they truly will be.

217
00:12:43,496 --> 00:12:46,659
This boat is my home.
You all are guests on it.

218
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:48,293
Guests?

219
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:50,899
Now, I earned my passage,
Captain--
(Mal)
And it's time...

220
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:52,767
your little sister learned
from your example.

221
00:12:52,838 --> 00:12:55,068
I have earned my passage...

222
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:58,974
treating bullet holes,
knife wounds, laser burns.

223
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:00,807
Some jobs are more
interesting than others.

224
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,848
And you want to put my sister
in the middle of that.

225
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:05,076
Didn't say "want."
Said "will."

226
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:06,812
It's one job, Doc.
She'll be fine.

227
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:09,446
She's a 17-year-old girl.

228
00:13:09,755 --> 00:13:12,417
A mentally
traumatized 17--
She's a reader.

229
00:13:12,858 --> 00:13:14,826
Sees into the truth
of things.

230
00:13:14,894 --> 00:13:17,624
Might see trouble
before it's coming.
Which is of use to me.

231
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:21,063
And that's your guiding star,
isn't it? What's of use.

232
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:25,125
Honestly, Doctor,
I think we may really
crash this time anyway.

233
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:27,529
Do you understand
what I have gone through...

234
00:13:27,606 --> 00:13:29,039
to keep River away
from the Alliance?

235
00:13:29,108 --> 00:13:31,668
I do, and it's a fact
we here have been courteous...

236
00:13:31,744 --> 00:13:33,302
enough to keep
to our own selves.

237
00:13:33,379 --> 00:13:36,507
Are you threatening to--
I look out for me and mine.

238
00:13:37,183 --> 00:13:40,448
That don't include you
less I conjure it does.

239
00:13:40,519 --> 00:13:43,682
You stuck a thorn
in the Alliance's paw.
That tickles me a bit.

240
00:13:43,756 --> 00:13:46,554
But it also means
I got to step
twice as fast to avoid them...

241
00:13:46,625 --> 00:13:49,093
and that means
turning down plenty of jobs.

242
00:13:49,161 --> 00:13:50,526
Even honest ones.

243
00:13:50,963 --> 00:13:53,227
Put this crew together with
the promise of work...

244
00:13:53,299 --> 00:13:55,494
[metal clanking]
which the Alliance makes
harder every year.

245
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:57,798
Come a day there
won't be room
for naughty men like us...

246
00:13:57,870 --> 00:13:59,394
to slip about at all.

247
00:13:59,572 --> 00:14:02,666
This job goes south,
there well may not be another.

248
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:06,140
So here is us,
on the raggedy edge.

249
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:10,708
Don't push me,
and I won't push you.

250
00:14:11,116 --> 00:14:12,913
[speaking Chinese]

251
00:14:25,497 --> 00:14:28,955
Zoe, Wash gonna straighten
this boat out before
we get flattened?

252
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:32,561
(Zoe)
Like a downy feather, sir.
No one flies like my mister.

253
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:34,603
[engine grinding]

254
00:14:35,174 --> 00:14:37,734
[Mal and Zoe chattering]

255
00:14:41,747 --> 00:14:42,736
(Simon)
River.

256
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:47,015
I know.
We're going for a ride.

257
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:51,053
[engine revving]

258
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,026
[people chattering]

259
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:08,430
Hey, little one.

260
00:15:09,808 --> 00:15:12,003
Understand your part
in all this?

261
00:15:14,346 --> 00:15:15,404
Do you?

262
00:15:17,149 --> 00:15:18,946
This is what I do, darling.

263
00:15:22,621 --> 00:15:24,020
This is what I do.

264
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:27,991
(Mal)
Let's move, people.

265
00:15:29,295 --> 00:15:31,763
Quit fiddling.
Want the boat running
smooth when we get back.

266
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:34,458
Have faith, Captain.
Not today.

267
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,368
Pair of clips
in the rear hatch.

268
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:41,198
We should hit town
right during Sunday worship.

269
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,604
Won't be any crowds.

270
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:44,973
If Fanty and Mingo
are right about the payroll...

271
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:47,103
this could look to be
a sunny day for us.

272
00:15:47,179 --> 00:15:49,079
(Simon)
River, stay behind the others.

273
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:52,174
If there's fighting,
drop to the floor or run away.

274
00:15:53,218 --> 00:15:55,209
It's okay
to leave them to die.

275
00:15:55,521 --> 00:15:59,013
Doctor, I'm taking your sister
under my protection here.

276
00:15:59,892 --> 00:16:01,587
If anything happens to her,
anything at all...

277
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:04,561
I swear to you
I will get very choked up.

278
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,621
Honestly.
There could be tears.

279
00:16:15,274 --> 00:16:19,472
Don't mind
the Captain none, Simon.
I know he'll look out for her.

280
00:16:20,112 --> 00:16:22,307
They'll be back
before you can spit.

281
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,452
Well, not that you spit.

282
00:16:32,925 --> 00:16:34,654
(Jayne)
What are we hoping
to find here...

283
00:16:34,727 --> 00:16:36,160
that equals
the worth of a turd?

284
00:16:36,228 --> 00:16:39,061
(Mal)
Security payroll. Alliance
don't have the manpower...

285
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:41,725
to "enforce the peace"
on every outer-rim planet.

286
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:45,065
They hire
out to the private firms,
who will not work for credit.

287
00:16:45,137 --> 00:16:48,573
They get paid in cashy money,
which once a month rests here.

288
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:50,665
Don't that lead back to
the Alliance, anyhow?

289
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:53,610
No private firm
would ever report the theft
of their own payroll.

290
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:56,842
They'd appear weak,
might lose their contract.

291
00:16:56,915 --> 00:17:00,544
Yeah, we're as ghosts in this.
Won't but rattle the floor.

292
00:17:00,619 --> 00:17:04,783
Shiny. Let's be bad guys.

293
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:07,916
Hands and knees and heads
bowed down! Everybody, down!

294
00:17:07,993 --> 00:17:09,153
[woman screaming]

295
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:11,218
[grunting]

296
00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:19,695
Looks like this is the place.

297
00:17:19,905 --> 00:17:23,466
You all wanna
be looking very intently
at your own belly buttons.

298
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:26,806
I see a head start to rise,
violence is going to ensue.

299
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:29,907
Probably guessed we mean
to be thieving here...

300
00:17:29,982 --> 00:17:32,143
but what we're after
is not yours.

301
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,876
So let's have
no undue fussing.

302
00:17:35,621 --> 00:17:36,952
She's locked up.

303
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:53,497
[people murmuring]

304
00:18:23,735 --> 00:18:26,203
Do you know what
the definition of a hero is?

305
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:29,100
Someone who gets
other people killed.

306
00:18:29,408 --> 00:18:31,137
You can look it up later.

307
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:36,313
Big happy family.

308
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:42,676
[beeping]

309
00:18:45,724 --> 00:18:49,216
At last.
We can retire and give up
this life of crime.

310
00:18:54,099 --> 00:18:55,430
[metal rattling]

311
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:56,790
Hey!

312
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:01,270
You all are Browncoats, eh?
Fought for independence?

313
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:03,399
Petty thieving
ain't exactly soldiers' work.

314
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:07,775
War's long done.
We're all just folk now.
Listen up!

315
00:19:08,514 --> 00:19:10,209
We are coming down
to empty that vault!

316
00:19:10,282 --> 00:19:13,149
(guard)
You have to give me
your authorization password!

317
00:19:17,222 --> 00:19:18,280
(guard)
Okay.

318
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,537
I'm telling you I heard it.
Repeater.

319
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:38,875
Did sound somewhat
like gun blast. Maybe
you ought run tell Lawman.

320
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:40,700
[screaming]

321
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,342
What the hell is up?
You all right?

322
00:19:45,150 --> 00:19:46,811
What's going on?

323
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:49,513
Reavers.

324
00:19:56,228 --> 00:19:59,857
The leg is good. It'll bleed
plenty and we avoid
any necessary organs.

325
00:19:59,932 --> 00:20:01,297
I was thinking
more of a graze.

326
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,197
No, you don't want it
to look like you gave up.

327
00:20:03,268 --> 00:20:04,462
No, I get that.

328
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:05,901
(Jayne)
Mal!

329
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,268
Every heist, he's got
to start yelling my name.

330
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:11,207
Mal! Reavers!

331
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:14,171
The girl's pitching a fit.
They're here
or they're coming soon.

332
00:20:14,246 --> 00:20:15,645
Get on the Mule.

333
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:18,512
Does that lock
from the inside?
Yes.

334
00:20:18,584 --> 00:20:21,075
Get everyone upstairs.
You get them down here
and you seal it.

335
00:20:21,153 --> 00:20:23,713
As long as you got air
you don't open up,
you understand?

336
00:20:23,789 --> 00:20:26,883
Get them inside the vault!

337
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:30,117
You see them?
Zoe, take the wheel!

338
00:20:30,195 --> 00:20:31,560
(Jayne)
Anybody see them?

339
00:20:38,036 --> 00:20:39,264
Take me with you!

340
00:20:39,338 --> 00:20:40,999
Get back in the vault with
the others.

341
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:44,008
I can't stay here! Please!
It's too many. Move ahead.

342
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,509
Please!

343
00:20:52,184 --> 00:20:53,276
[screaming]

344
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,957
[engine revving]

345
00:21:20,078 --> 00:21:22,569
Faster! Faster!
Faster would be better!

346
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:33,218
How come
they ain't blowing us
out the air?

347
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:36,159
They wanna run us down.
The up-close kill.

348
00:21:37,796 --> 00:21:39,991
They want us alive
when they eat us.

349
00:21:40,432 --> 00:21:44,425
Boy, sure would be nice
if we had some grenades,
don't you think?

350
00:21:44,569 --> 00:21:45,866
[gun firing]

351
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,099
Wash, baby, can you hear me?
We're moments from air.

352
00:21:49,174 --> 00:21:51,472
You got somebody
behind you?
Reavers.

353
00:21:53,779 --> 00:21:54,803
Kaylee!

354
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,677
Heat her up. We got Reavers.

355
00:22:00,752 --> 00:22:03,812
We're not gonna
get to you in time.
Keep moving, honey.

356
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:05,481
We're coming to you.

357
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:15,193
(Jayne)
Where's my clips?
(Mal)
Rear hatch.

358
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:16,656
[screaming]

359
00:22:24,443 --> 00:22:25,569
[groaning]

360
00:22:27,145 --> 00:22:28,635
[Jayne yelling]

361
00:22:30,816 --> 00:22:32,181
I won't get ate!

362
00:22:33,485 --> 00:22:37,922
You shoot me if they take me!
Well, don't shoot me first!

363
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:52,801
[grunting]

364
00:22:56,742 --> 00:22:58,733
Get some distance on them.

365
00:22:58,810 --> 00:23:01,608
You come to the flats,
I want you to swing round.

366
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:03,914
We're gonna try
a Barn Swallow.

367
00:23:03,982 --> 00:23:05,916
Simon! Open her up!

368
00:23:11,056 --> 00:23:12,523
(Mal)
They're closing on us!

369
00:23:12,591 --> 00:23:14,786
Those rocks,
give them a taste.

370
00:23:30,375 --> 00:23:32,741
(Wash)
Okay, baby,
we talked this through.

371
00:23:36,047 --> 00:23:37,605
Talking ain't doing.

372
00:23:37,682 --> 00:23:38,774
[speaking Chinese]

373
00:23:39,785 --> 00:23:40,774
[whooshing]

374
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:15,275
[grunting]

375
00:24:16,822 --> 00:24:17,846
[groaning]

376
00:24:17,923 --> 00:24:21,359
River?
I swallowed a bug.

377
00:24:25,831 --> 00:24:29,323
Are you okay?
Is he okay?

378
00:24:29,401 --> 00:24:30,390
[screeching]

379
00:24:42,647 --> 00:24:45,013
(Wash)
We all here? What's going on?

380
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:46,614
Hello?

381
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,382
No casualties.

382
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:53,180
Anybody following?
(Wash)
Nice flying, baby.

383
00:24:53,258 --> 00:24:55,692
That's a negative.
Clean getaway.

384
00:24:56,094 --> 00:25:00,428
Set course for Beaumonde.
First thing,
I want this body--

385
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:01,488
(Kaylee)
Simon!

386
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:04,362
[speaking Chinese]

387
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:06,266
You son of a whore.
I'm a hair's breadth...

388
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:07,669
from riddling
you with holes, Doctor.

389
00:25:07,739 --> 00:25:11,197
One simple job!
She'll be fine!
She is fine!

390
00:25:11,276 --> 00:25:13,403
Except for being still crazy,
she's a picture of health!

391
00:25:13,478 --> 00:25:17,175
Wasn't for River,
we'd probably be left there.
She felt them coming.

392
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:19,442
(Simon)
Never again.
You understand me?

393
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:22,316
Seems I remember a talk about
you giving orders on my boat.

394
00:25:22,387 --> 00:25:23,945
Well, we're off your boat.

395
00:25:24,022 --> 00:25:26,490
Just as soon as River
gets her share of the bounty.

396
00:25:26,558 --> 00:25:29,322
Let's not do anything hasty--
No, shiny!

397
00:25:29,594 --> 00:25:31,186
We'll be on Beaumonde
in 10 hours' time...

398
00:25:31,263 --> 00:25:34,130
you can pick up your earnings
and be on your merry.

399
00:25:34,399 --> 00:25:37,232
Meantime, you do your job.

400
00:25:38,136 --> 00:25:39,694
Patch up my crew.

401
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,667
He didn't lie down.

402
00:25:45,443 --> 00:25:47,104
They never lie down.

403
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:58,287
(Zoe)
No, I think things will glide
a deal smoother for us...

404
00:25:58,356 --> 00:26:00,324
without River
and Simon on board...

405
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:01,791
but how long
do you think they'll last?

406
00:26:01,860 --> 00:26:03,418
Doc made his call.

407
00:26:03,495 --> 00:26:04,484
Yeah.

408
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:06,394
They's as babes in a basket
when we took them in.

409
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:08,295
We sheltered them plenty.

410
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:11,699
Man has to cut loose,
learn to stand on his own.

411
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:15,369
Like that man back in town?

412
00:26:18,376 --> 00:26:19,775
I had to shoot him.

413
00:26:19,844 --> 00:26:21,835
What Reavers would've done
before they killed him--

414
00:26:21,913 --> 00:26:24,404
I know.
That was a piece of mercy.

415
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:28,219
But before that,
him begging us
to bring him along.

416
00:26:29,387 --> 00:26:32,322
We couldn't take the weight.
Would've slowed us down.

417
00:26:32,390 --> 00:26:35,655
You know that for certain?
Mule won't run with five.

418
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:40,059
I should've dumped the girl?
Or you? Or Jayne?

419
00:26:40,231 --> 00:26:41,528
Oh, Jayne....

420
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:45,298
You could've
tossed the payload.
Tossed the....

421
00:26:46,504 --> 00:26:50,270
Zoe, I got bits falling
off my ship, I got
a crew ain't been paid...

422
00:26:50,342 --> 00:26:53,311
and, oh, yeah, a powerful need
to eat sometime this month.

423
00:26:53,745 --> 00:26:55,440
We tell Fanty and Mingo
we skunked the job...

424
00:26:55,513 --> 00:26:57,504
what do think
they'll do to us?

425
00:26:59,384 --> 00:27:01,284
We're close to gone out here.

426
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:04,888
We get a job,
we got to make good.

427
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:08,085
Sir, I don't disagree
on any particular point.

428
00:27:09,861 --> 00:27:11,021
It's just...

429
00:27:14,199 --> 00:27:17,430
in the time of war,
we would've never
left a man stranded.

430
00:27:18,837 --> 00:27:20,566
Maybe that's why we lost.

431
00:27:29,948 --> 00:27:31,609
That was close.

432
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:35,317
(Jayne)
I do not get it.

433
00:27:36,187 --> 00:27:37,984
How's a guy get so wrong?

434
00:27:38,089 --> 00:27:41,547
Cutting on his own face,
raping and murdering.

435
00:27:44,462 --> 00:27:46,453
I'll kill a man
in a fair fight...

436
00:27:47,265 --> 00:27:49,790
or if I think
he's gonna
start a fair fight...

437
00:27:50,635 --> 00:27:54,162
or if he bothers me,
or if there's a woman...

438
00:27:54,606 --> 00:27:59,441
or if I'm getting paid.
Mostly only when
I'm getting paid.

439
00:28:00,612 --> 00:28:03,308
These Reavers,
the last 10 years...

440
00:28:03,381 --> 00:28:06,214
they show up like
the boogeyman from stories.

441
00:28:07,218 --> 00:28:10,517
Eating people alive?
Where does that get fun?

442
00:28:12,123 --> 00:28:14,455
Shepherd Book said
they was men who just...

443
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:17,893
reached the edge of space,
saw a vasty nothingness...

444
00:28:17,962 --> 00:28:19,953
and went
bibbledy over it.

445
00:28:20,098 --> 00:28:21,087
Oh, hell.

446
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:24,425
I've been to the edge.

447
00:28:25,136 --> 00:28:29,004
Just looked like more space.

448
00:28:30,008 --> 00:28:31,407
I don't know.

449
00:28:31,476 --> 00:28:33,842
It can get awful lonely
in the black.

450
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:38,605
Like to get addlepated
ourselves, we stay
on this boat much longer.

451
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:41,875
Captain will drive
us all off, one by one.

452
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:44,511
Just like Simon and River.

453
00:28:46,291 --> 00:28:47,758
Just like lnara.

454
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:51,894
Kaylee, are you ever going
to put that capture down?

455
00:28:51,996 --> 00:28:54,521
(Kaylee)
We got to have records
of everything, Inara.

456
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:58,467
A bona fide companion
entertained clients
on this very ship.

457
00:28:59,003 --> 00:29:02,370
In this very bed.
Well, I can't do my work here.

458
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,465
And I don't think
the Captain approves.

459
00:29:04,542 --> 00:29:06,134
The Captain
wants you to stay--

460
00:29:06,211 --> 00:29:09,578
That man doesn't
know what he wants.
I don't have time to....

461
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:28,497
**[music playing]

462
00:29:38,076 --> 00:29:40,237
[people chattering]

463
00:29:43,748 --> 00:29:46,273
(woman)
Don't talk to the barkers,
talk to the captains.

464
00:29:46,351 --> 00:29:49,752
You look the captain
in the eye.
Know who you're dealing with.

465
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:51,845
I wish there was....

466
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:57,521
You shouldn't
ought to be so clean.

467
00:29:57,962 --> 00:30:01,454
It's a dead giveaway
you don't belong,
you always got to be tidy.

468
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:03,467
Don't pay anybody in advance.

469
00:30:05,136 --> 00:30:07,627
And don't ride in anything
with a Capissen 38 engine...

470
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:09,696
they fall right
out of the sky.

471
00:30:10,375 --> 00:30:11,740
Kaylee.

472
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:25,349
River, do you want
to stay with them?

473
00:30:26,991 --> 00:30:28,549
It isn't safe.

474
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:31,284
No.

475
00:30:33,598 --> 00:30:35,691
I fear it isn't safe anymore.

476
00:30:38,203 --> 00:30:39,397
For them.

477
00:30:41,806 --> 00:30:44,104
[people clamoring]

478
00:30:57,088 --> 00:30:59,352
(man on TV)
...only survivors
of the massacre apparently...

479
00:30:59,424 --> 00:31:02,188
Iocked themselves in
the train station vault.

480
00:31:02,260 --> 00:31:05,252
Kaylee,
this is a place of business.
We can talk about Simon when--

481
00:31:05,330 --> 00:31:06,797
When he's
four worlds away?

482
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:09,197
Or the Alliance gets a hold
of him and River?

483
00:31:09,267 --> 00:31:10,325
(Mal)
That ain't my worry.

484
00:31:10,401 --> 00:31:12,699
I got to finish this job
and get us another one.

485
00:31:12,770 --> 00:31:14,601
Can't do that
carrying those two.

486
00:31:15,006 --> 00:31:16,906
(Kaylee)
How can you be so cold?

487
00:31:16,975 --> 00:31:19,136
Captain didn't
make them fugitives.

488
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:21,405
But he could
have made them family.

489
00:31:21,579 --> 00:31:24,377
Instead of keeping Simon
from seeing I was there.

490
00:31:25,116 --> 00:31:28,017
When I carried such a torch,
when we could've....

491
00:31:28,586 --> 00:31:31,419
We're going on a year now,
