00:48:41,084 --> 00:48:43,177
Yeah, you left, um....

740
00:48:43,553 --> 00:48:45,282
Got some of your
stuff in a trunk.

741
00:48:45,355 --> 00:48:46,879
I never did get a chance
to drop it off.

742
00:48:46,957 --> 00:48:51,223
I didn't mean to leave stuff.
I didn't look
through the stuff.

743
00:48:51,595 --> 00:48:54,758
I just....
Just sundries I expect.

744
00:48:57,668 --> 00:49:00,466
So I'll send you a wave,
soon as I can.

745
00:49:01,204 --> 00:49:02,364
Thank you.

746
00:49:11,315 --> 00:49:14,182
Inara, nice to see
her again.

747
00:49:16,153 --> 00:49:18,519
So, trap?
Trap.

748
00:49:19,056 --> 00:49:21,718
We going in?
Only but a few hours out.

749
00:49:22,326 --> 00:49:25,318
Yeah, but, remember the part
where it's a trap?

750
00:49:25,529 --> 00:49:27,963
If that's the case,
then lnara's already
caught in it.

751
00:49:28,031 --> 00:49:30,022
She wouldn't
set us up willing.

752
00:49:30,267 --> 00:49:33,134
Might be we got a shot
at seeing who's
turning these wheels.

753
00:49:33,203 --> 00:49:34,227
We go in.

754
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:37,637
But how can you be sure
lnara don't just
wanna see you?

755
00:49:38,575 --> 00:49:40,975
Sometimes people
have feelings.

756
00:49:41,144 --> 00:49:43,169
I'm referring here to people.

757
00:49:44,948 --> 00:49:47,041
You all were watching,
I take it.

758
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:50,715
Yes.
Did you see us fight?

759
00:49:50,954 --> 00:49:52,512
No.
Trap.

760
00:50:00,497 --> 00:50:04,331
We're about 70 miles
from the Training House,
and nobody on radar.

761
00:50:04,401 --> 00:50:06,869
If the Alliance is about,
they're laying low.

762
00:50:06,937 --> 00:50:08,097
They're about.

763
00:50:08,171 --> 00:50:10,196
Find us a home.
I'll take the shuttle
a little closer.

764
00:50:10,273 --> 00:50:11,934
Zoe, ship is yours.

765
00:50:12,009 --> 00:50:14,534
Remember. If anything
happens to me...

766
00:50:14,611 --> 00:50:16,340
or if you don't hear from me
within the hour...

767
00:50:16,413 --> 00:50:18,677
you take this ship
and you come
and you rescue me.

768
00:50:18,749 --> 00:50:19,738
What?

769
00:50:20,384 --> 00:50:22,682
Risk my ship?
I mean it.

770
00:50:23,120 --> 00:50:25,850
It's cold out there.
And I don't wanna get left.

771
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:46,073
Dear Buddha,
please bring me a pony,
and a plastic rocket, and--

772
00:50:46,143 --> 00:50:48,043
Mal! What are you
doing here?

773
00:50:48,645 --> 00:50:49,839
Well, you invited me.

774
00:50:49,913 --> 00:50:52,473
I never thought for a second
you'd be stupid enough
to come.

775
00:50:52,549 --> 00:50:54,414
Well, that makes you
kind of a tease, doesn't it?

776
00:50:54,484 --> 00:50:56,418
You knew my invitation
wasn't on the level.

777
00:50:56,486 --> 00:50:59,455
Which led me to conclude
that you must be
in some trouble.

778
00:50:59,523 --> 00:51:01,286
I'm fine. I'm giddy.

779
00:51:01,358 --> 00:51:03,792
For a woman schooled
in telling a man
what he wants to hear...

780
00:51:03,860 --> 00:51:07,352
you ain't much of a liar.
Mal, you cannot
handle this man.

781
00:51:13,437 --> 00:51:14,597
I have to say, Captain...

782
00:51:14,671 --> 00:51:17,538
I'm impressed that you
would come for her yourself.

783
00:51:17,874 --> 00:51:20,968
And that you would make it
this far, in that outfit.

784
00:51:22,145 --> 00:51:24,443
I can be very graceful
when I need to.

785
00:51:24,514 --> 00:51:25,879
I've no doubt.

786
00:51:27,284 --> 00:51:29,980
What are you doing?
I'm praying for you, Mal.

787
00:51:30,720 --> 00:51:32,483
She's very thoughtful.

788
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:35,892
But I mean it when I say
I've no intent to harm you.

789
00:51:36,660 --> 00:51:38,287
Speak your piece.

790
00:51:38,762 --> 00:51:40,627
I think you're
beginning to understand...

791
00:51:40,697 --> 00:51:42,665
how dangerous River Tam is.

792
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,830
She is a mite unpredictable.

793
00:51:45,102 --> 00:51:47,002
Mood swings, of a sort.

794
00:51:47,070 --> 00:51:49,595
It's worse than you know.
It usually is.

795
00:51:49,673 --> 00:51:53,302
That girl will
rain destruction down
on you and your ship.

796
00:51:54,711 --> 00:51:57,475
She is an albatross, Captain.

797
00:51:57,647 --> 00:51:59,376
Way I remember it...

798
00:51:59,483 --> 00:52:02,816
albatross was
a ship's good luck,
till some idiot killed it.

799
00:52:03,353 --> 00:52:06,049
Yes, I've read a poem.
Try not to faint.

800
00:52:06,590 --> 00:52:08,421
I've seen your war record.

801
00:52:09,392 --> 00:52:11,952
I know how you must feel about
the Alliance.

802
00:52:12,229 --> 00:52:14,424
You really don't.
Fair to say.

803
00:52:15,165 --> 00:52:17,998
But I have to hope
you understand,
you can't beat us.

804
00:52:18,068 --> 00:52:19,797
I got no need to beat you.

805
00:52:19,870 --> 00:52:22,737
I just want to go my way.
And you can do that...

806
00:52:23,573 --> 00:52:26,599
once you let me take
River Tam back home.

807
00:52:30,313 --> 00:52:32,838
No, no. You're working
this deal all crabbed.

808
00:52:32,949 --> 00:52:35,645
You got to open with payment.
That is a trap.

809
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:39,346
I offer money,
you'll play the man of honor
and take umbrage.

810
00:52:39,556 --> 00:52:42,184
I ask you to do what is right,
you'll play the brigand.

811
00:52:42,259 --> 00:52:44,784
I have no stomach for games.

812
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:47,286
I already know
you will not see reason.

813
00:52:47,364 --> 00:52:48,922
The Alliance wanted to
show me a reason...

814
00:52:48,999 --> 00:52:51,194
they shouldn't have sent
an assassin.

815
00:52:57,440 --> 00:53:00,534
I have a warship
in deep orbit, Captain.

816
00:53:01,211 --> 00:53:04,738
We locked on
to Serenity's pulse beacon
the moment you hit atmo.

817
00:53:04,881 --> 00:53:06,906
I can speak a word
and send a missile...

818
00:53:06,983 --> 00:53:09,679
to that exact location
inside of three minutes.

819
00:53:09,753 --> 00:53:10,913
You do that...

820
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:14,889
you'd best make peace
with your dear
and fluffy lord.

821
00:53:18,662 --> 00:53:19,890
Pulse beacon.

822
00:53:20,163 --> 00:53:24,122
Advice from an old tracker.
You want to find someone,
use your eyes.

823
00:53:24,668 --> 00:53:26,932
How long do you think
you can really run from us?

824
00:53:27,003 --> 00:53:29,631
I never credited
the Alliance with
an overabundance of brains.

825
00:53:29,706 --> 00:53:31,867
And if you're
the best they got--
Captain Reynolds...

826
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:34,740
I should tell you,
so that you don't
waste your time...

827
00:53:34,811 --> 00:53:38,770
you can't make me angry.
Please, spend
an hour with him.

828
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:42,313
I want to resolve this
like civilized men.

829
00:53:43,386 --> 00:53:45,286
I'm not threatening you.

830
00:53:45,655 --> 00:53:47,122
I'm unarmed.
Good.

831
00:53:47,190 --> 00:53:48,384
[gun firing]

832
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,288
I am, of course,
wearing full body armor.

833
00:53:54,364 --> 00:53:56,696
I am not a moron.
(lnara)
Wait, just let--

834
00:53:56,766 --> 00:53:58,256
[all grunting]

835
00:54:05,976 --> 00:54:06,965
[groans]

836
00:54:13,550 --> 00:54:14,847
[glass shattering]

837
00:54:14,918 --> 00:54:16,317
[groaning]

838
00:54:20,056 --> 00:54:21,045
[panting]

839
00:54:22,425 --> 00:54:23,687
[gasping]

840
00:54:24,894 --> 00:54:26,384
What, no backup?

841
00:54:26,896 --> 00:54:30,093
Making an awful ruckus.
They'll come
when they're needed.

842
00:54:30,166 --> 00:54:31,599
I'd start whistling.

843
00:54:31,735 --> 00:54:34,898
Captain, what do you think
is going to happen here?

844
00:54:37,707 --> 00:54:39,334
[both grunting]

845
00:54:59,362 --> 00:55:00,795
[lnara groans]

846
00:55:04,501 --> 00:55:05,798
[groans]

847
00:55:10,774 --> 00:55:12,264
[glass shatters]

848
00:55:19,582 --> 00:55:20,981
[panting]

849
00:55:21,751 --> 00:55:26,051
Nothing here is what it seems.
He isn't the plucky hero.

850
00:55:26,890 --> 00:55:30,849
The Alliance isn't
some evil empire.
This is not the grand arena.

851
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,721
And that's not incense.

852
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:38,324
[beeping]

853
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:40,930
Sir, can you hear me?

854
00:55:41,004 --> 00:55:43,529
Just a flash bomb. Go. Go!

855
00:55:44,207 --> 00:55:46,334
[lnara and Mal grunting]

856
00:55:49,245 --> 00:55:52,476
What have you done
to my shuttle?
It's not your shuttle.

857
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,714
Head east. Keep her low.

858
00:55:54,884 --> 00:55:56,476
[engine revving]

859
00:56:10,567 --> 00:56:12,364
Okay, forget
the pulse beacon.

860
00:56:12,435 --> 00:56:14,596
There must be another way
to track the ship.

861
00:56:14,671 --> 00:56:16,070
Get a read
on the nav. sat.

862
00:56:16,139 --> 00:56:18,699
It's a registered transport,
you must be able to locate.

863
00:56:18,775 --> 00:56:19,764
(ensign)
Sir?

864
00:56:19,843 --> 00:56:21,708
Yes, have you found
a nav. sat. trajectory?

865
00:56:21,778 --> 00:56:24,212
Sir, we found seven.

866
00:56:31,955 --> 00:56:33,684
(Inara)
We've every reason
to be afraid.

867
00:56:34,090 --> 00:56:37,082
Why, 'cause this guy
beat up Mal?
That ain't so hard.

868
00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:39,685
He didn't beat me up.
Nobody said that.

869
00:56:39,763 --> 00:56:41,526
Because he's a believer.

870
00:56:41,765 --> 00:56:46,202
He's intelligent, methodical,
and devout in his belief...

871
00:56:46,269 --> 00:56:48,669
that killing River
is the right thing to do.

872
00:56:48,738 --> 00:56:51,298
So no hope
of a reward, huh?

873
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:55,678
Did he say anything
about a Miranda?

874
00:56:56,479 --> 00:56:57,537
What is that?

875
00:56:57,614 --> 00:57:00,014
Don't know who or what,
but it's on River's mind.

876
00:57:00,083 --> 00:57:02,074
Conjure it might be the reason
they're after her.

877
00:57:02,152 --> 00:57:05,053
You think maybe it poses
some kind of threat
to the Alliance?

878
00:57:05,121 --> 00:57:06,486
Do we care?

879
00:57:06,890 --> 00:57:08,585
Are we caring about that?

880
00:57:08,658 --> 00:57:11,320
You dumb-ass hogs,
the only people
she's a threat to is...

881
00:57:11,394 --> 00:57:12,884
us on this boat.

882
00:57:12,962 --> 00:57:14,793
Look, we get back
to Haven...

883
00:57:14,864 --> 00:57:15,888
in a few
hours' time.
Oh, yeah.

884
00:57:15,965 --> 00:57:17,262
Hiding under
the Shepherd's skirts...

885
00:57:17,333 --> 00:57:18,357
that's a manful scheme.

886
00:57:18,435 --> 00:57:20,460
You wanna run this ship?
Yes.

887
00:57:21,538 --> 00:57:23,335
Well, you can't.

888
00:57:24,073 --> 00:57:26,268
Do a damn sight
better job than you.

889
00:57:26,376 --> 00:57:28,810
Getting us lashed over
a couple of strays.

890
00:57:29,045 --> 00:57:31,036
No offense, Doc.
I think it's
noble as a grape...

891
00:57:31,114 --> 00:57:32,342
the way you look to River.

892
00:57:32,415 --> 00:57:34,883
But she ain't my sister
and she ain't your crew.

893
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:37,317
Oh, and neither is she
exactly helpless.

894
00:57:37,687 --> 00:57:40,212
So, where's it writ
that we got to lay down
our lives for her?

895
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:41,848
Which is what you've
steered us toward.

896
00:57:41,925 --> 00:57:43,654
I didn't start this.

897
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:45,818
No, that's right.

898
00:57:46,663 --> 00:57:50,326
Alliance starts the war,
and then you volunteer.

899
00:57:52,268 --> 00:57:53,963
Battle of Serenity, Mal.

900
00:57:54,037 --> 00:57:57,268
Besides Zoe here, how many....
Hey, I'm talking at you.

901
00:58:01,311 --> 00:58:04,337
How many men in your platoon
came out of there alive?

902
00:58:07,584 --> 00:58:09,711
You wanna leave this room.

903
00:58:12,555 --> 00:58:14,284
Damn right, I do.

904
00:58:21,631 --> 00:58:23,656
This isn't
the war, Mal.

905
00:58:24,534 --> 00:58:26,764
You telling me that
'cause you think I don't know?

906
00:58:26,836 --> 00:58:28,963
You came to the Training House
looking for a fight.

907
00:58:29,038 --> 00:58:30,938
I came looking for you.

908
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,710
I just want to know
who I'm dealing with.

909
00:58:34,811 --> 00:58:37,439
I've seen too many versions
of you to be sure.

910
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:41,946
I start fighting a war,
I guarantee
you'll see something new.

911
00:58:49,125 --> 00:58:50,353
We'll get off.

912
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:52,053
River and I will
get off at Haven.

913
00:58:52,128 --> 00:58:53,891
We'll find some--
Nobody's saying that.

914
00:58:53,963 --> 00:58:55,794
Nobody besides Jayne
is saying that.

915
00:58:55,865 --> 00:58:56,854
Mal.

916
00:58:59,335 --> 00:59:02,429
I got no answers
for you, lnara.
I got no rudder.

917
00:59:02,505 --> 00:59:05,474
Wind blows northerly,
I go north.
That's who I am.

918
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:08,102
Now, maybe that ain't
a man to lead,
but they have to follow.

919
00:59:08,177 --> 00:59:09,269
So you wanna tear me down...

920
00:59:09,345 --> 00:59:11,506
do it inside your own mind.
I'm not trying
to tear you down.

921
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:13,173
But you fog things up.

922
00:59:13,983 --> 00:59:15,678
You always have.

923
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:18,753
You spin me about.

924
00:59:21,958 --> 00:59:24,119
I wish like hell
you was elsewhere.

925
00:59:26,329 --> 00:59:27,421
I was.

926
01:00:01,731 --> 01:00:03,062
[rumbling]

927
01:00:18,314 --> 01:00:20,407
[flies buzzing]

928
01:00:23,019 --> 01:00:24,179
[gasps]

929
01:00:48,044 --> 01:00:49,272
[speaking Chinese]

930
01:00:58,388 --> 01:00:59,753
[beeping]

931
01:01:00,556 --> 01:01:02,820
No trouble,
little crazy person.

932
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:08,194
We're going
for a nice shuttle ride.

933
01:01:11,834 --> 01:01:13,028
[gun fires]

934
01:01:20,877 --> 01:01:22,777
[doorknob rattling]

935
01:01:25,715 --> 01:01:27,512
She's out. Jayne's down.

936
01:01:27,717 --> 01:01:30,242
The other way.
Find her and do not engage.

